While we were waiting for the police to come to check for prints, I decided to toprope-clean the route because that would take the least time and might be in time before the police would arrive. The toprope ascent was easy and felt as if it would have been an easy lead climb as well. The route is awesome with almost only positive holds. Crux is a bit harder, but doable. Could be 7b+. This route has it all, slab, tufas big jugs and overhang!

name: Esterattitude
comment:
Nice climb. Doable. 2nd go - ripped off a hold and fell. 3rd go - slipped and belayer fell. 4th go next day - not warmed up enough / too stressed...


For next time:

From the start: Two side-underclings to the first bolt (1). Adjust left hand so it’s more an undercling. Skip the shitty hold for your left hand but reach up high with your right to the good jug. Left hand to tufa blob, same blob on right side with you right hand. Clip the draw with your right hand (2). High right thin tufa with right hand, left thin tufa with left hand. Clip with right hand (3). Big gray tufa with both hands. Continue with left hand higher up the tufa. Right hand as well, semi good hold. Reposition your feet on the small spots right and left of the tufa. Right hand on left side of the tufa. Left hand goes up high, just above the tufa, pinch with open hand. Left foot goes higher on the white-ish smeared hold left of the tufa. Right hand high on the 3 finger sloperish but OK hold right of the next bolt. Reposition your right foot. Left foot on the tufa, right foot higher. Again left foot higher on the tufa. Stand up and reach all the way up with your left hand to the hold left of the bolt. Clip with your right hand (4). Work your way up to the small ledge optionally using the side hold for your right hand on the right.  Both hands on the ledge, stand up high, reach your left hand all the way up to the good hold higher up. Clip with right hand (5). From here on it’s easy. Continue a bit left and up, clip the next draw (6). Continue up and to the right to the anchor. 9 draws on total.
